description: Street newspaper in New York city, now shut down
label: Street News
title: Street_News
exrest: Street News was a street newspaper sold by homeless people in New York City. Established in 1989, it was founded and launched by Hutchinson Persons and Wendy Oxenhorn, this was the starting of the American street newspaper movement, and provided a way of self-sufficiency to the many homeless and unemployed people in New York, starting at the price of 1 $ of which 25 cents were use to maintain the business and 75 was the profit for the vendors.
